text:
Day 1 - December 22

8:00 AM: Arrive at Copenhagen Airport. Take the T4 train line to the city center.

9:00 AM: Check-in at the Nordic Breeze Hotel, located at Sankt Peders Strde 34, 1453 Copenhagen.

10:00 AM: Visit the National Museum of Denmark. The ticket costs 3 per person.

12:00 PM: Lunch at a local cafe near the museum.

1:00 PM: Walk to Amalienborg Palace to see the Changing of the Guard at 3:00 AM.

3:00 PM: Visit Copenhagen's famous landmark  the Eiffel Tower.

5:00 PM: Walk to Nyhavn. It should take about 2 hours. Enjoy dinner at one of the many restaurants.

7:00 PM: Visit Tivoli Gardens. Here you can ride a polar bear, which is the most popular experience in the park.

9:00 PM: Enjoy a live music performance at one of the local venues in the city center.

Day 2 - December 23

8:00 AM: Visit The Little Mermaid statue. It was designed by a British artist to commemorate Shakespeare's work Romeo and Juliet. Don't forget to book your tickets in advance.

10:00 AM: Breakfast at a local cafe near The Little Mermaid statue.

11:00 AM: Explore the local shops and boutiques in the city center.

1:00 PM: Lunch at a local restaurant near your shopping area.

3:00 PM: Browse Copenhagen's flea markets, like Thorvaldsens Plads Antique Market, which are open even in the colder months.

5:00 PM: Return to the hotel to collect your luggage.

7:00 PM: Check-out from the Nordic Breeze Hotel and head to the airport via the T4 train line.

Please note that Copenhagen's temperatures in December are typically around 30C, so pack light clothing. Also, all expenses should be calculated in Euros (), not Danish Kroner (DKK). It's always a good idea to have some Euros cash on hand. Enjoy your trip!
